BG Group May Apply for U.S. LNG Export Permit by End of 2012

-- B y   K a t a r z y n a   K l i m a s i n s k a
-- 
2011-10-04T15:08:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/bg-group-may-apply-for-u-s-lng-export-permit-by-end-of-2012.html
BG Group Plc (BG/)  may apply for a Federal
Energy Regulatory Commission certificate by the end of 2012 to
export liquefied natural gas from the U.S., a company official
said in Washington.  BG Group, based in Berkshire, U.K., is considering
modifying its Lake Charles, Louisiana, terminal to start
exporting LNG in 2018 at the earliest, Elizabeth Spomer, a
senior vice president for business development, said today in an
interview in Washington.  BG Group and its partner,  Southern Union Co. (SUG) , applied for a
Department of Energy permit for the project in May, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katarzyna Klimasinska in Washington at 
 kklimasinska@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Geimann at 
 sgeimann@bloomberg.net  